ds_queue_head: This function will only read the first value of the queue (that which is "at the head"). It will not dequeue the value, meaning that it can still be read in the future by this function or the ds_queue_dequeue(). If the queue is empty then the function will return the constant undefined, otherwise it will return the real or string value contained in the queue.
